Firstly, in a large bown, take carrot, cabbage, spring onion and ginger garlic paste
Add 1 tsp chilli sauce and salt, mix well
Add 2 tsp Maida, 2 tsp cornflour and mix well
Form a soft dough adding maida if required
Prepare a small ball sized balls
Deep fry in hot oil until the balls turn golden brown
Now, in a large Kadai, heat 2 tsp oil and saute ginger, garlic, chilli and spring onion
Add onion and fry on high flame
Add capsicum and fry till shrinks slightly
Add vinegar, soy sauce, chilli sauce, tomato ketchup, pepper powder and salt
Fry till all the sauces are well combined
Add 1 cup water and boil on medium flame
In a small bowl take 2 tsp cornflour and water
Mix well forming a lump-free slurry
Pour in cornflour slurry and mix well
Continue to boil until the gravy thickens and turns glossy
Add in prepared veg manchurian balls and spring onions and mix well
Serve hot Veg Manchurian.